{
  "stem": "26790.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We young people like I was, we're standing on the ground on the footpath and listen to the radio to the news, the music.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We enjoyed, but who ever buy a radio?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But my boss have a radio.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because he was well-off, he bought a radio.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A radio was [? a sort of ?] big box like this television.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And from this radio, you can hear from all over the world-- capital cities all over the world.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He just pressed the button, it [INAUDIBLE], he put on Berlin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Here was Berlin's [? sign. ?] Hitler speaking, from nine o'clock in the morning till twelve o'clock in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was speaking non-stop.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't think [INAUDIBLE] I pick up the glass [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because he never stopped for a second.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And what he was talking, us German language and Yiddish language, some words are similar.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I understand what he was saying.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was saying, the bloody Jewish, they are everywhere.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They are the banks, they are the business, they are the government.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They make for trouble for all over the world.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We will get rid of them, that's what we understand a few words.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Seven o'clock, he finished-- I say he finished barking.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I call-- say barking [INAUDIBLE] something like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I say he finished barking.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Seven o'clock, my boss say, Mojsze, they will put on [? there ?] Warsaw, capital city for Poland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "After they put on Warsaw, we hear already different sort of things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And this time when Hitler was speaking from nine o'clock in the morning till twelve, and this time the German Army crossed the border without any-- without any-- declaring war.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they already occupied this town, mentioned the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they mentioned [INAUDIBLE] how many people got killed, how many-- how many buildings was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
